SIMPLE: wallet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wallet
<hw>Wal"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>walet</ets>,
probably the same word as OE. <ets>watel</ets> a bag. See
<er>Wattle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bag or sack for carrying
about the person, as a bag for carrying the necessaries for a journey; a
knapsack; a beggar's receptacle for charity; a peddler's pack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[His hood] was trussed up in his <qex>walet</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pocketbook for keeping money about the
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything protuberant and swagging.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wallets</xex> of flesh.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Walleteer</ent>⟦br⟧
